main event: Radar detected a large target at an unusually high altitude with sudden changes in altitude at tremendous speeds on 12 Feb 62.
interesting points: The radar tracked the target for about 5 minutes before it disappeared due to scope limitations., The object was recorded at a height exceeding 74,000 feet., Analysis determined that the object was definite for further evaluation., The target was described as bright due to its height., Two individuals with significant radar experience were involved in the observation.
witness description: SSGT Grover F. (Crew Chief, GSS Radar 99) with 11 years of radar experience and A/2C Charles Wood, both from the same address.
